main event: A radar and visual observation of a high-speed maneuvering object over the Azores on September 16, 1959.
interesting points: The observation lasted 30 minutes and involved one object that disappeared at 20,000 ft.,The airborne object was green-white in color and traveled at speeds of 500 mph.,Radar confirmed the visual sighting of the object, which maneuvered at high altitude.,The object was estimated to be around 30,000 ft during its flight path.,Pilots believed the sighting could be a rocket, missile, or falling star, but ruled out a falling star due to its speed.
witness description: John R. Taft, 1st Lt, pilot at Dover AFB, and another pilot in MATS aircraft
